                <div class="text-center text-justify justified wow fadeInDown">
                    <p>
                        The village is famous for <b>Lord Shri Mahalingeshwara</b> and <b>Shri Mahaganapathi</b> temple.
                        The annual fair of the temple is celebrated with great charm and devotion. And on this day chariot of the temple is pulled by many devotees with statues of god placed in it. Ganesh Chaturthi is the holiest day in this village. Thousands of devotees visit this temple on that day and offer their prayers. Devotees firmly believe that Lord Mahaganapathi bless them and fulfills their wishes.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Special poojas and celebrations are held during the <b><i>Ganesh Chaturthi</i></b> during which nearly 5000 devotees visit the temple and participate in (<b><i>annasantarpane</i></b>), that is served on that day. Besides religious functions, cultural events are also organised on the Ganesh Chaturthi day in the temple. On the day of Ekadashi the meals are not served, the people maintain fast and offer prayers to god. During Meena in the month of Marchâ€“April, on the full moon day the festivities start with the hoisting of the temple flag and Rathotsava is also organised on that day. On Tuesdays and <i>Sankashti</i>, more number of devotees visits the temple. 
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        In December month, daily <i>bhajana</i> is conducted by <b>Pernankila Bhajana Mandali</b> at each houses in the village. At the end, on last saturday of December Bhajana Mangala is held in temple. During this, many other bhajana groups comes to the event and performs. This program starts at 6pm and ends at next morning 6am.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        It is believed that the Pernankila Shri Mahaganapati is fond of <b><i>appams</i></b> prepared out of rice, coconut, ghee and jaggery. On the Ganesh Chaturthi day nearly one quintal rice is used to prepare one lac appams and distribute among the devotees. The <b><i>kopparige appa</i></b> is seva provided, where devotees offer prayers to god and <i>annasantharpane</i> is done. 
                    </p>
